text: Tomah is a city in Monroe County, Wisconsin, United States. The population was 9,570 as of the 2020 census. Tomah was founded by Robert E. Gillett in 1855 and incorporated as a city in 1883 but the charter was not issued until 1894. ==References== Category:Cities in Wisconsin Category:Monroe County, Wisconsin Category:1855 establishments in Wisconsin
title: Tomah, Wisconsin
